The paper proposes a general approach to visual generation that combines learning capabilities with logic descriptions of the target to be generated. The approach involves the use of deep architectures to model the involved variables and a computational scheme where the learning process carries out a satisfaction of the constraints. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it deals with visual generation. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes the modeling of GAN and auto-encoders, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category.
